      "content": "ok that makes sense. so if i want to pay it off faster, i should aim to pay more than the minimum so more of my money hits the principal directly. but i'm worried about these hidden fees or extra costs that might pop up later and mess up my math. are there any common things like that i should watch out for so the balance doesn't just creep back up?",
